question:
What is logged to the console after approximately 100ms for each iteration?
```javascript
for (var i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
  setTimeout(function() {
    console.log(i);
  }, 100);
}
```

What will be the output of the following code?
```javascript
const user = {
  name: "Alice",
  greet: function() {
    return `Hello, my name is ${this.name}`;
  }
};
const sayHello = user.greet;
console.log(user.greet());
console.log(sayHello());
```
